Q. Do you know the man that hired the cart of you? - A. I do not; a gentleman came to me in Thames-street, about four o'clock, on a Friday, about six weeks ago, it was a holiday at the Custom-house, and asked me if I had a cart to spare; I told him, yes; I had just sent one home, and went after it;
William Gould
drove the cart; when I got the cart back, he told me to drive it into the Tower; I went with my man up as far as the White Tower, the further end; these goods laid on the pavement, and he told me to turn the cart round where the casks lay.
